item.title: Ford Company Layoffs Ford Company Job Cuts and Business Future
item.description: Ford, one of the largest automakers in the world, has announced significant job cuts at its Detroit-area factory building electric pickup trucks. This is part of a larger trend of job cuts in the auto industry, driven by the transition to electric vehicles. Nearly 8,000 workers are expected to be affected at various auto plants, making it the deepest reduction in jobs since the late 1970s. item.description: ESPN‘s highly coveted sports analysis show, First Take, will be getting a facelift on June 4. The show will be taking on a new format with full time hosts Stephen A. Smith and Skip Bayless going head-to-head for hot topic debates. Smith was previously featured as a guest on the morning program but will now appear on the reformatted show 5-days a week. “We tweaked the show format last year to focus more on debate and specifically on presenting and challenging Skip’s opinions and we saw our viewers respond to that change,” said Jamie Horowitz, ESPN’s vice president of original programming and production.

item.title: Teen Charged In Fatal School Shooting Of Courtlin Arrington
item.description: An Alabama teenager has been charged with manslaughter and illegal gun possession for the death of Courtlin Arrington in what is the third fatal high school shooting of the year. AL reports the shooting happened Wednesday (Mar. 7) at Huffman High School in Birmingham, Ala. as students were being let out of school. Arrington was shot in chest by Michael Jerome Barber. The teen was given CPR at the scene but died 30 minutes later. Barber also shot himself in the leg at the time of the shooting.

item.title: Selena Gomez Addresses Water Weight Gain From Medication
item.description: Real talk!Selena Gomez clapped back at body-shamers who have attacked her appearance — and revealed that her lupus medication causes her weight fluctuations.  “I tend to hold a lot of water weight and that happens very normally. And then when I’m off of [my medication], I tend to lose weight,” Gomez, 30, explained during a TikTok Live videothat was shared via Twitter on Thursday, February 16. “I just wanted to say and encourage anyone out there who feels any sort of shame for exactly what they’re going for and nobody knows the real story — I just want people to know that you’re beautiful and you’re wonderful and, yeah, maybe we have days where we feel like s—t but I would much rather be healthy and take care of myself.

item.description: Name:Jamie-Lynn Sigler Hometown:Jericho, NY Birthday:May 15, 1981 About Costume design: Perhaps not quite as style shape-shifting as her roles — Tony Soprano’s daughter to Turtle’s girlfriend to a punk, hipster assistant on Ugly Betty this fall — the Long Island-raised Sigler, 28, says she too loves “to play and dress my mood. Sometimes I feel a bit more downtown bohemian, lots of jewelry, big earrings, dresses. And sometimes I go ‘uptown,’ with preppier polos and khakis.

item.title: Laurie Hernandez Details Post-Gymnastics Life With Partner Charlotte
item.description: Laurie Hernandez may have retired from gymnastics competition in 2021, but the Olympic gold medalist and her partner, Charlotte Drury, are just getting started. “Both of us kind of eased out of sports [after the 2020 Tokyo Olympics]. We moved to New York and then got into the arts,” Hernandez, 24, told Us Weekly exclusively while promoting On Location Olympic hospitality packages. “It’s just nice for us to have the chance to explore what else outside of sports we might be into and test out all these different waters.

item.title: Morgan Wallen's Ex KT Smith Marries Luke Scornavacco
item.description: Morgan Wallen’s ex-fiancée, Katie “KT” Smith, has found new love with Luke Scornavacco. Smith announced via Instagram that she and Scornavacco tied the knot just days after announcing their engagement on March 30. “Swipe for a surprise 🤎🌼,” Smith captioned an April 4 slideshow featuring a farm photo shoot of the duo and Smith’s son, Indigo, 3, whom she shares with Wallen, 30. Smith broke her marriage news in the post’s last slide by sharing a snap of herself holding a marriage certificate with her new husband.

item.title: Paul Kynman
item.description: Paul Kynman is a demandable and successful actor in the film industry. He is known for the movies and television projects like ‘First Knight (1995), Clash of Titans (2010), Casualty (1998-2013), Doctors (2007-2012), and many more. His role as Bevington and Hephaestus in the movie First Knight and Clash of Titans became popular worldwide. Also, he has worked in documentary shows as well. According to IMDB, he has credits for more than 50 television dramas and movies.

item.title: The Spiritual Meaning of a Lunar New Year Lantern Festival
item.description: "Michelle, do you want me to send you some bunny lanterns? Yes, I will send you half a dozen, and you can use them or give them to your friends." I can’t help but giggle as I read my mom’s last text message to me. I’m a capable, independent adult in my thirties, and she’s concerned I’m not able to procure the necessities to celebrate the upcoming Lantern Festival, honoring the Year of the Rabbit.

item.title: Tia Mowry Salary, Net Worth, Age, Height, Movies And TV Shows, Christmas Movie
item.description: Tia Mowry is an American actress.  She was born on July 6, 1978, in Gelnhausen, West Germany, to Darlene and Timothy Mowry. Tia began entering pageants and talent shows while their family was stationed at Fort Hood, Texas. She is well known for playing Tia Landry, a twin separated at birth and reunited with her sisters as a teenager in the show, Sister, Sister. In September 2021, Tia released her second cookbook, The Quick Fix Kitchen, published by Rodale Books.

item.title: New Boko Haram Video Reveals Kidnapped Girls
item.description: A Nigerian journalist shared a Boko Haram  video on social media Sunday (Aug. 14) reportedly revealing several Nigerian girls captured by the terrorist group more than two years ago. According to the New York Times, the unidentified Boko Haram fighter who appears in the nearly 12-minute video claims some of the girls were killed in air strikes implemented by the Nigerian to battle on-going terrorism. “They should know that their children are still in our hands,” the masked man purportedly states while holding a rifle in hand.

item.title: Sarah Jessica Parker Bangs by Serge Normant: Details, Tips
item.description: Much like her beloved Sex and the City character, Sarah Jessica Parker’s perfectly tousled locks are an institution. Needless to say, our interest was piqued when Parker stepped out for an appearance on the Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon on Tuesday, February 6, sporting new honey blonde highlights and side bangs. We love the idea of a chic side bang — especially when it is Carrie Bradshaw-approved — so we went straight to Parker’s mane man, hairstylist Serge Normant, to get all the details on the new ‘do.

item.title: Scheana Shay Addresses Hugging Tom Sandoval in 'Pump Rules' Beach Pics
item.description: Scheana Shay hinted that there’s more to the story after fans slammed the Vanderpump Rules cast for hugging Tom Sandoval in recent beach photos. “All these people saying they aren’t gonna watch the season from photos that have been coming out … like come on!” Scheana, 38, replied via Instagram on Friday, August 11, on a fan account showing Lala Kent embracing Sandoval, 41, on the sand. “How about you WATCH the damn show and see HOW all these photos happened!

item.title: Selena Gomez Doesnt Approve Of Taylor Swifts New Romance With Travis Kelce
item.description: Highlights Selena Gomez is concerned about Taylor Swift's relationship with NFL star Travis Kelce, questioning his intentions. Selena confronted Taylor about her concerns, wanting her to see things from a different perspective and discuss the romance. Travis Kelce's past, including a reality TV show where he dated 50 women and allegations of cheating, adds to Selena's skepticism. Taylor Swift has made it known how important her girl squad is, but that doesn’t mean she needs everyone’s approval when it comes to her dating life.

The crew got the boots from no other than Jay Z himself. “Jay Z was pulling up in his Maybach, right? You know how Def Jam was on the side of the Universal building at the time?

item.title: Who Is Billy Napiers Wife Ali Napier?
item.description: Billy Napier is a 42-year-old American football coach who has won the 2019 Sun Belt Coach of the Year. Billy Napier is into college football coaching and he is the current head coach for the Florida Gators of the University of Florida. Billy Napier has been versatile and has served in various coaching roles for the likes of the University of Louisiana, Arizona State University, Colorado State, and others. Prior to becoming a coach, Billy Napier played as a quarterback for the Murray County High School and the Furman University.

item.title: Bachelor's Maquel Cooper Says She, Ex-Husband Josh Are 'Soulmates'
item.description: Never say never! Maquel Cooper, who competed for the affection of Arie Luyendyk Jr. on season 22 of The Bachelor, hinted that she’s open to reconciling her relationship with her ex-husband, Josh Munday. “We aren’t together at the moment,” she tells Us Weekly exclusively. “We’ve had an on-again, off-again relationship for the past 10 years.” Still, the reality star, 24, says there’s still hope for the two of them. “Currently we are off, but I wouldn’t put it past us to get back together in the future,” she confesses.

item.title: Bachelorette Sneak Peek: Jenn Tran Takes Men to Melbourne Race Track
item.description: Bachelorette Jenn Tran is an adventurous woman, hoping to find a partner to match her energy. “I’m feeling some adrenaline right now. I’m not a gown’s girl; I’m more of a jumpsuits, sneakers, let’s get down and dirty [type],” Jenn, 26, says in Us Weekly’s exclusive sneak peek of the Monday, July 22, episode of The Bachelorette. Jenn invited her contestants Hakeem Moulton, Austin Ott, Aaron Erb and Jeremy Simon to a local race track in Melbourne for a high-speed group date.
